Although Service Desk team are able to view the SLA details in the JIRA tickets, too many SLA metrics listed there could be causing unnecessary confusion. 

For example, support agent might only need to view on SLA of Time to Resolution. Additional SLA metrics are not used by the support agent but used by other category of users from Service Desk Team.

There's also use case of user which grant some high level customer to view the JIRA tickets created by their organization users:
{quote}
-          publish the agreed SLA details  like “ time to first response “ for the customer, they have accounts and can browse their company tickets

-          collect additional interesting metrics, like “ Time waiting for support “. Additional metrics doesn’t necessarily have to show in any ticket view as long it can be reported, even only using the API.
{quote}

