As of current release of SD, there are no feature to calculate a life cycle for an issue and the only possible way to workaround this is by calculating the work logged plus the waiting for support time.

There are situations where customers would like to know the cycle time of each issue is handled to perform comparison to the known issues to improvise the cycle time and set better accuracy SLAs.

*Below is the actual quote from customer*
{quote}
This is one of the requirements that we have in our SLA policy, so that if the issue was resolved, closed then reopened for example then resolved again we need to know the total time the issue took from creation till closure even with multiple reopening or closing since the response and resolution times are always reset. It is a requirement from our customers and it helps later in estimating similar issues
{quote}

