There should be a reference or link to a Customer Portal request from the associated JIRA issue. While, it makes sense that the other aspects of JIRA is isolated from the Customer Portal, It's a different thing while working in JIRA and you need to find the URL of the SD request. 

This is the use case described by a customer who raised this:
{code}
we also communicate about tickets with customers through other means like email and Skype. Its is then very convenient for the customer to get a direct link to the ticket instead of having to search for it by themselves. For us we are then also sure we are talking about the same ticket.
{code}

It doesn't appear efficient to have to search in Service Desk for the corresponding Request for an issue you're already working on in JIRA, and this can be improved by simply providing the URL reference of the SD request in a JIRA issue field.

